1
00:01:42,840 --> 00:01:46,840
=Such A Good Love=

2
00:01:47,380 --> 00:01:50,220
=Episode 4=

3
00:01:50,370 --> 00:01:53,219
(Spring 2008, Beijing)

4
00:01:53,220 --> 00:01:56,969
(Spring 2008, Beijing)
Your job is to sell aphrodisiac liquor.

5
00:01:56,970 --> 00:01:58,579
(Cordyceps Men's Vitality Tonic)

6
00:01:58,580 --> 00:02:01,409
So you have to be enthusiastic

7
00:02:01,410 --> 00:02:02,459
and passionate.

8
00:02:02,460 --> 00:02:03,520
Got it?

9
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:05,760
Give us a second.

10
00:02:05,970 --> 00:02:06,769
Wait.

11
00:02:06,770 --> 00:02:09,040
My friend didn't tell me
we'd be selling this stuff.

12
00:02:09,530 --> 00:02:11,360
I don't think we can do this.

13
00:02:12,220 --> 00:02:14,880
This... This doesn't seem very proper.

14
00:02:15,220 --> 00:02:15,849
Forget it.

15
00:02:15,850 --> 00:02:16,760
Well.

16
00:02:20,780 --> 00:02:22,970
How much does it pay?

17
00:02:23,570 --> 00:02:24,779
No base salary.

18
00:02:24,780 --> 00:02:27,250
Twenty yuan commission
for every bottle sold.

19
00:02:27,620 --> 00:02:28,730
Twenty?

20
00:02:29,060 --> 00:02:30,219
Twenty?

21
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:31,250
Are you down or not?

22
00:02:31,570 --> 00:02:32,345
- Yes!
- Yes!

23
00:02:32,346 --> 00:02:36,619
(Cordyceps Men's Vitality Tonic)

24
00:02:36,620 --> 00:02:37,899
What is this?

25
00:02:37,900 --> 00:02:39,080
What are you selling?

26
00:02:39,546 --> 00:02:41,496
What a fair girl.

27
00:02:43,500 --> 00:02:45,619
Young lady,
care to introduce your product?

28
00:02:45,620 --> 00:02:49,179
This is
Turtle Sage Men's Vitality Tonic.

29
00:02:49,180 --> 00:02:50,339
Aphrodisiac?

30
00:02:50,340 --> 00:02:51,779
How does it work?

31
00:02:51,780 --> 00:02:53,819
Tell me about it.

32
00:02:53,820 --> 00:02:56,010
I... I'm not sure.

33
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:58,730
You don't know what you're selling?

34
00:02:58,850 --> 00:03:01,819
I just want to know
if this really helps.

35
00:03:01,820 --> 00:03:02,129
Mister,

36
00:03:02,130 --> 00:03:04,450
she said she doesn't know.

37
00:03:05,130 --> 00:03:07,409
Let me explain. I know all about it.

38
00:03:07,410 --> 00:03:08,529
Have you ever seen

39
00:03:08,530 --> 00:03:10,410
Beijing at 3 AM?

40
00:03:10,660 --> 00:03:11,569
I'm asleep by then.

41
00:03:11,570 --> 00:03:12,969
Exactly.

42
00:03:12,970 --> 00:03:14,099
Take two bottles home,

43
00:03:14,100 --> 00:03:15,880
and I guarantee

44
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:19,779
you'll see Beijing at 3 AM, mister.

45
00:03:19,780 --> 00:03:21,409
- For real?
- Well, then. I'll take one.

46
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:22,249
That's not enough.

47
00:03:22,250 --> 00:03:24,379
One will only get you to 1:30 AM.

48
00:03:24,380 --> 00:03:26,320
You need two to see 3 AM.

49
00:03:26,450 --> 00:03:27,730
Give me two.

50
00:03:27,900 --> 00:03:29,379
No rush.

51
00:03:29,380 --> 00:03:30,289
- Daji.
- 100 yuan.

52
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,849
You're surprisingly bold.

53
00:03:31,850 --> 00:03:32,339
No choice.

54
00:03:32,340 --> 00:03:33,880
I have an artist to feed.

55
00:03:37,100 --> 00:03:37,970
Mister,

56
00:03:38,220 --> 00:03:39,880
may I ask you some questions?

57
00:04:03,970 --> 00:04:05,819
(The Third Health Care
Life Culture Exhibition)

58
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:06,920
Jingshu,

59
00:04:07,010 --> 00:04:07,939
both of us made 200 yuan

60
00:04:07,940 --> 00:04:09,939
in just one day.

61
00:04:09,940 --> 00:04:12,600
A few days more of this, we'll have
enough money to pay the rent.

62
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:15,200
You've introduced a great gig for me.

63
00:04:15,860 --> 00:04:17,689
There's a little downside.

64
00:04:17,690 --> 00:04:19,890
Those fellows were
saying disgusting things.

65
00:04:20,090 --> 00:04:21,530
You know what?

66
00:04:21,570 --> 00:04:23,539
This kind of money is easy to make

67
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:25,440
if you don't mind
setting your pride aside.

68
00:04:25,770 --> 00:04:27,890
But I think pride is important.

69
00:04:28,090 --> 00:04:30,290
It means nothing if it's for love.

70
00:04:34,650 --> 00:04:36,170
Zhou Shui is here for you.

71
00:04:45,180 --> 00:04:46,850
He's so handsome.

72
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:50,890
Not bad.

73
00:05:01,060 --> 00:05:02,240
Zhou Shui!

74
00:05:03,980 --> 00:05:04,569
Jingshu.

75
00:05:04,570 --> 00:05:05,539
Daji!

76
00:05:05,540 --> 00:05:06,770
Zhou Shui!

77
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:09,210
Zhou Shui.

78
00:05:10,770 --> 00:05:12,249
You're off work.

79
00:05:12,250 --> 00:05:13,089
How was your day?

80
00:05:13,090 --> 00:05:15,059
Um... Zhou Shui came to
pick up Daji from work,

81
00:05:15,060 --> 00:05:17,680
and I was worried he'd be walking alone,
so I tagged along.

82
00:05:18,060 --> 00:05:20,240
He's a grown man.
What's there to worry about?

83
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:22,120
He's worried about your safety.

84
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:23,889
Just tell her.

85
00:05:23,890 --> 00:05:25,129
Don't be shy.

86
00:05:25,130 --> 00:05:26,290
What about you?

87
00:05:26,380 --> 00:05:28,000
Why are you here?

88
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:29,530
I missed you.

89
00:05:34,090 --> 00:05:34,979
Let's go home.

90
00:05:34,980 --> 00:05:36,170
- Let's go home.
- Let's go.

91
00:05:58,060 --> 00:06:00,400
There's somewhere I need to be.

92
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:02,059
It's true. Zhou Shui,
is it something urgent?

93
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:04,329
- No, you have nothing to do now.
- I really do, Dumbbell.

94
00:06:04,330 --> 00:06:05,440
It's true.

95
00:06:05,650 --> 00:06:07,089
Send Jingshu home.

96
00:06:07,090 --> 00:06:08,209
Please take care of Dumbbell.

97
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:09,179
Get home safely.

98
00:06:09,180 --> 00:06:09,859
Is this okay?

99
00:06:09,860 --> 00:06:10,739
Yes.

100
00:06:10,740 --> 00:06:12,089
Of course.

101
00:06:12,090 --> 00:06:13,330
Take care.

102
00:06:14,130 --> 00:06:15,440
We're in a hurry.

103
00:06:16,380 --> 00:06:18,210
He doesn't have plans, though.

104
00:06:20,210 --> 00:06:21,360
Let's go.

105
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:29,129
You're always busy with school,

106
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:30,970
why take on so many jobs?

107
00:06:31,820 --> 00:06:33,210
Do you really need money?

108
00:06:33,940 --> 00:06:36,530
Everyone living
in Chunzhili Residence does.

109
00:06:38,860 --> 00:06:40,040
True.

110
00:06:41,500 --> 00:06:42,249
But I think

111
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:43,730
you're pushing yourself too hard.

112
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,129
I come from a village.

113
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:46,600
I have a younger brother.

114
00:06:47,500 --> 00:06:50,440
My parents didn't want me
to go to Beijing to study.

115
00:06:52,620 --> 00:06:54,440
They never give me a dime.

116
00:06:54,540 --> 00:06:56,419
My tuition is covered by student loans.

117
00:06:56,420 --> 00:06:58,800
And I have to earn money to pay
my living expenses.

118
00:07:00,540 --> 00:07:03,170
Plus, I have to send money back
every month.

119
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:06,600
That's tough for you.

120
00:07:07,380 --> 00:07:08,770
No.

121
00:07:09,250 --> 00:07:11,560
Studying in Beijing is my dream.

122
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:13,680
I'm happy now.

123
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:19,120
Actually, I'm also happy.

124
00:07:20,010 --> 00:07:21,120
Sorry?

125
00:07:22,060 --> 00:07:23,170
I mean,

126
00:07:23,500 --> 00:07:25,689
everyone came here to chase their dream.

127
00:07:25,690 --> 00:07:27,730
And the entire process

128
00:07:27,770 --> 00:07:29,209
means happiness,

129
00:07:29,210 --> 00:07:30,360
doesn't it?

130
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:35,240
Then why do you want to become
someone like Schwarzenegger?

131
00:07:36,010 --> 00:07:37,890
My parents passed away when I was a kid.

132
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,560
I'm an orphan.

133
00:07:40,010 --> 00:07:41,560
My uncle raised me.

134
00:07:42,420 --> 00:07:42,939
One time,

135
00:07:42,940 --> 00:07:45,330
he took me to a record store
in the county town.

136
00:07:46,010 --> 00:07:47,059
That's where

137
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:48,730
I met Schwarzenegger.

138
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:51,440
From then on, I had a dream.

139
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:53,650
I wanted to be

140
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:56,090
a strong man like him.

141
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:03,419
That's great.

142
00:08:03,420 --> 00:08:06,480
Let's strive for our dreams.

143
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:12,290
Are you heading home now?

144
00:08:14,010 --> 00:08:15,560
Aren't you?

145
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:20,090
You go back first.

146
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:24,600
Where are you going?

147
00:08:24,890 --> 00:08:26,040
I...

148
00:08:27,210 --> 00:08:29,000
I'm going for a run.

149
00:08:34,210 --> 00:08:35,779
Why do you always go running

150
00:08:35,780 --> 00:08:37,410
when I'm home?

151
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:39,680
Are you afraid of me?

152
00:08:40,140 --> 00:08:41,890
No, it's not that.

153
00:08:42,210 --> 00:08:43,080
I...

154
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:48,170
I'm afraid I won't be able
to control myself.

155
00:08:53,660 --> 00:08:56,899
See this, Director Zhou?

156
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:59,130
Two red bills.

157
00:08:59,210 --> 00:09:00,209
My today's earnings.

158
00:09:00,210 --> 00:09:02,139
I also filmed

159
00:09:02,140 --> 00:09:03,179
something great today.

160
00:09:03,180 --> 00:09:04,960
- I'll show you later.
- Sure.

161
00:09:05,330 --> 00:09:06,369
What is this place?

162
00:09:06,370 --> 00:09:07,659
(China Film Art Research Center)

163
00:09:07,660 --> 00:09:09,530
China Film Archive.

164
00:09:09,690 --> 00:09:11,729
This is a holy place
for all Chinese moviemakers.

165
00:09:11,730 --> 00:09:14,179
They screen a lot of classic films here.

166
00:09:14,180 --> 00:09:16,449
There's a long line.
There must be a movie playing right now.

167
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:17,080
Let's go.

168
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:18,250
Let's go.

169
00:09:21,370 --> 00:09:22,410
What's that?

170
00:09:24,940 --> 00:09:26,019
It's awesome!

171
00:09:26,020 --> 00:09:27,819
- "Pulp Fiction"!
- "Pulp Fiction"!

172
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:28,899
My favorite!

173
00:09:28,900 --> 00:09:30,720
I haven't watched it yet.

174
00:09:31,180 --> 00:09:33,170
Zhou Shui, look at my outfit.

175
00:09:33,260 --> 00:09:34,200
Mia.

176
00:09:34,260 --> 00:09:35,539
That's the character!

177
00:09:35,540 --> 00:09:36,449
Let's go watch it.

178
00:09:36,450 --> 00:09:37,329
Hold on.

179
00:09:37,330 --> 00:09:38,729
(100 yuan per ticket)

180
00:09:38,730 --> 00:09:40,320
100 yuan per person.

181
00:09:40,780 --> 00:09:42,089
That's perfect.

182
00:09:42,090 --> 00:09:44,089
I have 200 yuan today.

183
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:44,539
I know.

184
00:09:44,540 --> 00:09:46,490
But all your earnings will be gone then.

185
00:09:46,780 --> 00:09:48,250
What's more important, money or movies?

186
00:09:52,210 --> 00:09:52,969
Wait.

187
00:09:52,970 --> 00:09:54,130
Get in line.

188
00:10:25,540 --> 00:10:27,489
(Zhou Shui's passion and determination)

189
00:10:27,490 --> 00:10:29,840
(are like a magnet
that keeps pulling me in.)

190
00:10:31,450 --> 00:10:34,290
(It took me many years to realize)

191
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,800
(that I wasn't just romantic hopeless.)

192
00:10:37,060 --> 00:10:38,840
(It was a banner.)

193
00:10:39,090 --> 00:10:40,369
- What does that mean?
- It means

194
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:42,019
that even though he has his own style,

195
00:10:42,020 --> 00:10:43,960
it's also something everyone can accept.

196
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:45,360
Especially that dance scene.

197
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,669
- The dance scene.
- What do you think?

198
00:10:46,669 --> 00:10:48,779
- Awesome, right?
- Incredible. This is my first time

199
00:10:48,780 --> 00:10:51,729
watching the two leads dancing
in the original film. It's cool.

200
00:10:51,730 --> 00:10:53,259
We can dance just as well.

201
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:54,890
Can we?

202
00:11:54,730 --> 00:11:56,200
(Our joy)

203
00:11:56,330 --> 00:11:58,320
(can be found in every street and alley
in Beijing.)

204
00:11:59,260 --> 00:12:01,370
(Back then, we had nothing,)

205
00:12:01,690 --> 00:12:03,329
(but we never bowed our heads.)

206
00:12:03,330 --> 00:12:09,680
(China Film Archive)

207
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:13,019
(Cordyceps Men's Vitality Tonic)

208
00:12:13,020 --> 00:12:13,899
Daji,

209
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:16,650
we made 800 yuan in just three days.

210
00:12:16,730 --> 00:12:17,449
That's incredible.

211
00:12:17,450 --> 00:12:18,840
You're amazing.

212
00:12:19,660 --> 00:12:20,299
Do you think

213
00:12:20,300 --> 00:12:22,779
I should open my own store?

214
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:24,089
Maybe I could be rich

215
00:12:24,090 --> 00:12:25,920
and keep a director.

216
00:12:26,260 --> 00:12:27,209
That could work.

217
00:12:27,210 --> 00:12:28,969
Remember to look out for me
when you get rich.

218
00:12:28,970 --> 00:12:30,019
Of course.

219
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:31,609
I got your back.

220
00:12:31,610 --> 00:12:33,040
All of you.

221
00:12:40,780 --> 00:12:42,569
Hello? What's wrong, Dongting?

222
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:44,200
You can't reach her?

223
00:12:44,540 --> 00:12:47,130
Jingjing and I are in our dorm.

224
00:12:47,540 --> 00:12:48,920
She's taking a shower.

225
00:12:51,490 --> 00:12:54,200
Okay. Coming.

226
00:12:55,730 --> 00:12:57,489
I need your help now, Daji.

227
00:12:57,490 --> 00:12:58,299
So suddenly?

228
00:12:58,300 --> 00:12:59,410
Let's go.

229
00:13:00,690 --> 00:13:02,720
What's going on? Why are you in a hurry?

230
00:13:04,330 --> 00:13:05,320
Here's what happened.

231
00:13:05,320 --> 00:13:06,329
The girl who rents my bed

232
00:13:06,330 --> 00:13:09,969
is meeting a boy right now, but her boyfriend
is on his way to see her.

233
00:13:09,970 --> 00:13:10,779
Wait.

234
00:13:10,780 --> 00:13:11,920
How many people are there?

235
00:13:12,450 --> 00:13:13,490
Three.

236
00:13:13,730 --> 00:13:14,819
No way. No.

237
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:16,329
You can't help her.

238
00:13:16,330 --> 00:13:17,609
This is a trouble.

239
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:20,130
If her boyfriend finds out,
he'll kill you.

240
00:13:20,570 --> 00:13:22,530
I don't have a choice.
I did this for her before.

241
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:25,440
Daji, I need you to pull this off.

242
00:13:26,090 --> 00:13:27,250
Me?

243
00:13:27,540 --> 00:13:28,650
Dongting.

244
00:13:28,690 --> 00:13:31,280
- Sorry to keep you waiting.
- Jingshu. What took you so long?

245
00:13:31,280 --> 00:13:32,939
- Where's Jingjing?
- She's on her period.

246
00:13:32,940 --> 00:13:34,059
She's feeling unwell.

247
00:13:34,060 --> 00:13:35,969
I made her brown sugar tea just now.

248
00:13:35,970 --> 00:13:37,659
Why isn't she picking up my calls?

249
00:13:37,660 --> 00:13:38,849
She's been sleeping.

250
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:40,610
Her phone is on silent mode.

251
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:43,680
Jingjing, wave to Dongting.

252
00:13:47,490 --> 00:13:48,899
She asks me to apologize.

253
00:13:48,900 --> 00:13:50,539
She really can't come down today.

254
00:13:50,540 --> 00:13:51,259
I'm so sorry.

255
00:13:51,260 --> 00:13:51,729
This...

256
00:13:51,730 --> 00:13:52,729
I'll pass it on to her.

257
00:13:52,730 --> 00:13:53,819
Okay.

258
00:13:53,820 --> 00:13:54,720
Oh, right.

259
00:13:56,820 --> 00:13:59,179
You missed the Number Theory lecture
last time.

260
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:01,419
I wrote down the key points
the professor went over.

261
00:14:01,420 --> 00:14:03,610
Remember to read it.
It's going to be in the final.

262
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,290
Thank you.

263
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:10,179
Jingshu, what's your connection
to Jingjing?

264
00:14:10,180 --> 00:14:14,019
- Why do you have to help her with this?
- Well. She rents my bed in our dorm.

265
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,059
Does that include
her love relationships?

266
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:18,609
Well, I charge her a high rent.
What if she doesn't rent from me?

267
00:14:18,610 --> 00:14:20,299
You're smart.

268
00:14:20,300 --> 00:14:21,610
Fair enough.

269
00:14:22,060 --> 00:14:22,419
Ma'am.

270
00:14:22,420 --> 00:14:24,179
Where were you?

271
00:14:24,180 --> 00:14:24,969
We're sorry.

272
00:14:24,970 --> 00:14:26,299
I had something at school...

273
00:14:26,300 --> 00:14:29,139
Enough. I don't want to hear it.
No commission for you today.

274
00:14:29,140 --> 00:14:30,560
Why?

275
00:14:31,210 --> 00:14:33,449
You two were gone the whole day,

276
00:14:33,450 --> 00:14:34,729
and you still want to get paid?

277
00:14:34,730 --> 00:14:36,059
It wasn't the entire day.

278
00:14:36,060 --> 00:14:37,179
We left at noon.

