00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:56,370
Leave me alone.

566
00:25:01,520 --> 00:25:03,040
(Welcome to Beijing)
Are you not happy?

567
00:25:04,980 --> 00:25:07,170
Keep silent. Thank you.

568
00:25:07,980 --> 00:25:10,520
I feel like I need to explain.

569
00:25:11,410 --> 00:25:12,610
Reverb

570
00:25:12,780 --> 00:25:14,440
is really a friend from my hometown.

571
00:25:14,500 --> 00:25:17,130
She brought me to a band before.

572
00:25:17,170 --> 00:25:18,720
But aside from that...

573
00:25:19,850 --> 00:25:22,650
You think I'm that petty?

574
00:25:23,090 --> 00:25:25,059
Can you stop talking?

575
00:25:25,060 --> 00:25:27,169
You're interrupting my thoughts.

576
00:25:27,170 --> 00:25:28,129
You're thinking?

577
00:25:28,130 --> 00:25:28,609
Yes.

578
00:25:28,610 --> 00:25:30,000
What are you thinking about?

579
00:25:32,980 --> 00:25:34,499
I shouldn't have brought you
to her place.

580
00:25:34,500 --> 00:25:35,200
No.

581
00:25:36,740 --> 00:25:38,000
You should.

582
00:25:39,460 --> 00:25:40,569
By visiting her house,

583
00:25:40,570 --> 00:25:41,779
I can now know

584
00:25:41,780 --> 00:25:43,810
what kind of house we want
in the future.

585
00:25:45,460 --> 00:25:46,200
No.

586
00:25:46,850 --> 00:25:49,130
We want something better.

587
00:25:50,570 --> 00:25:51,720
How so?

588
00:25:52,330 --> 00:25:53,480
First of all,

589
00:25:53,700 --> 00:25:55,059
the location has to be good,

590
00:25:55,060 --> 00:25:55,779
right?

591
00:25:55,780 --> 00:25:57,889
We can't settle for any place.

592
00:25:57,890 --> 00:25:59,019
I think

593
00:25:59,020 --> 00:26:00,520
we should buy

594
00:26:02,020 --> 00:26:03,499
next to this building.

595
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:04,779
And the floor

596
00:26:04,780 --> 00:26:06,089
needs to be good as well.

597
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:06,539
Okay.

598
00:26:06,540 --> 00:26:07,299
88th floors.

599
00:26:07,300 --> 00:26:09,369
88th. Straight up to the sky.

600
00:26:09,370 --> 00:26:10,259
One floor isn't enough.

601
00:26:10,260 --> 00:26:10,739
No problem.

602
00:26:10,740 --> 00:26:12,499
- Let's get two floors.
- Two floors.

603
00:26:12,500 --> 00:26:13,720
Two floors are ours.

604
00:26:13,780 --> 00:26:14,849
Good.

605
00:26:14,850 --> 00:26:16,169
Next is the bedroom.

606
00:26:16,170 --> 00:26:17,520
The bedroom

607
00:26:17,570 --> 00:26:18,810
will be right here.

608
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:19,889
Okay. This is our bedroom.

609
00:26:19,890 --> 00:26:21,840
- Our bed needs to be special.
- How special is it?

610
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:24,699
It's not like two single beds put together.

611
00:26:24,700 --> 00:26:26,569
It's a real double bed.

612
00:26:26,570 --> 00:26:28,170
Let me measure it.

613
00:26:28,540 --> 00:26:32,019
One, two, three, four, five,

614
00:26:32,020 --> 00:26:35,090
six, seven, eight, nine, ten.

615
00:26:35,260 --> 00:26:37,760
- Ten meters of bed.
- Ten meters of bed.

616
00:26:38,220 --> 00:26:40,129
Let's roll on it.

617
00:26:40,130 --> 00:26:41,850
We'll roll around.

618
00:26:41,890 --> 00:26:42,699
Over there.

619
00:26:42,700 --> 00:26:43,810
Right here.

620
00:26:43,820 --> 00:26:46,610
There's a huge floor-to-ceiling window,

621
00:26:46,820 --> 00:26:50,200
- and outside, we can see that!
- and outside, we can see that!

622
00:26:52,500 --> 00:26:54,929
- The bathroom will be over there.
- Bathroom. Right here.

623
00:26:54,930 --> 00:26:57,059
There's a huge tub.

624
00:26:57,060 --> 00:26:57,459
Good.

625
00:26:57,460 --> 00:26:59,369
We don't have to wait in line.

626
00:26:59,370 --> 00:27:00,920
Hot water is always available.

627
00:27:01,130 --> 00:27:01,779
No need to wait.

628
00:27:01,780 --> 00:27:04,219
Free and unlimited hot water.

629
00:27:04,220 --> 00:27:05,610
That's right.

630
00:27:05,820 --> 00:27:06,649
Here,

631
00:27:06,650 --> 00:27:08,539
the biggest space is our living room.

632
00:27:08,540 --> 00:27:09,649
Living room.

633
00:27:09,650 --> 00:27:10,699
How big is it?

634
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:11,920
Let me feel it.

635
00:27:11,980 --> 00:27:13,050
Measure it.

636
00:27:24,460 --> 00:27:25,499
Three, four.

637
00:27:25,500 --> 00:27:26,920
- How big?
- How big?

638
00:27:27,330 --> 00:27:31,000
- 240 square meters.
- 240 square meters.

639
00:27:31,130 --> 00:27:33,499
I want to cover all the walls and floor

640
00:27:33,500 --> 00:27:34,979
in the living room

641
00:27:34,980 --> 00:27:36,929
with your movie posters.

642
00:27:36,930 --> 00:27:38,299
Can I place a display case here?

643
00:27:38,300 --> 00:27:38,819
Yes.

644
00:27:38,820 --> 00:27:39,649
Look.

645
00:27:39,650 --> 00:27:42,059
Golden Bear, Golden Lion, Palme d'Or,

646
00:27:42,060 --> 00:27:43,499
Cannes, Berlin, and Busan awards!

647
00:27:43,500 --> 00:27:47,330
- The case isn't enough.
- I'll win them all.

648
00:27:47,740 --> 00:27:53,019
- Careful. The elevator isn't fully fixed yet.
- This is our home elevator.

649
00:27:53,020 --> 00:27:54,440
Home elevator.

650
00:27:56,820 --> 00:27:59,050
Sir, welcome home.

651
00:28:04,913 --> 00:28:06,500
♪Is it worth it?♪

652
00:28:06,570 --> 00:28:08,130
It's so beautiful tonight.

653
00:28:09,370 --> 00:28:10,650
So beautiful.

654
00:28:12,106 --> 00:28:13,756
♪Is it worth it?♪

655
00:28:13,757 --> 00:28:18,056
♪To turn back at every crossroads♪

656
00:28:19,146 --> 00:28:20,812
♪Is it worth it?♪

657
00:28:21,020 --> 00:28:24,330
This should be our movie room.

658
00:28:24,540 --> 00:28:27,409
We'll put a project here.

659
00:28:27,410 --> 00:28:30,280
The entire Beijing.

660
00:28:30,700 --> 00:28:32,169
Beijing

661
00:28:32,170 --> 00:28:33,369
is in our pocket.

662
00:28:33,370 --> 00:28:36,000
So, what do we need to do now?

663
00:28:37,130 --> 00:28:38,330
Well...

664
00:28:40,244 --> 00:28:41,903
♪Do you dare?♪

665
00:28:42,060 --> 00:28:43,170
Let's have a drink.

666
00:28:43,570 --> 00:28:44,849
Oh, you mean to have a drink.

667
00:28:44,850 --> 00:28:47,570
- What were you thinking about?
- How disappointing.

668
00:28:48,740 --> 00:28:50,130
Cheers.

669
00:28:54,410 --> 00:28:55,370
It feels so great.

670
00:28:55,500 --> 00:28:57,779
This is the life we should be living.

671
00:28:57,780 --> 00:28:59,369
This is the life

672
00:28:59,370 --> 00:29:00,739
we should have together.

673
00:29:00,740 --> 00:29:01,810
Daji,

674
00:29:01,890 --> 00:29:04,200
I'll make sure you live like this.

675
00:29:04,850 --> 00:29:05,369
Do you think

676
00:29:05,370 --> 00:29:06,779
we will still be us

677
00:29:06,780 --> 00:29:08,410
after having a life like this?

678
00:29:08,460 --> 00:29:09,520
Of course.

679
00:29:14,410 --> 00:29:16,219
Of course.

680
00:29:16,220 --> 00:29:17,699
We'll always be us.

681
00:29:17,700 --> 00:29:19,459
Forever us.

682
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:24,599
♪Luckily, we have been brave
ever since we met♪

683
00:29:24,600 --> 00:29:29,641
♪Perhaps that day means forever♪

684
00:29:30,368 --> 00:29:33,763
♪Outruning time,
leaving the past behind♪

685
00:29:33,764 --> 00:29:38,556
♪Later, the ocean drifted far away♪

686
00:29:38,557 --> 00:29:43,923
♪Even the waves grew tired♪

687
00:29:43,924 --> 00:29:47,450
♪The coldest days once burned
like blazing flames♪

688
00:29:47,451 --> 00:29:54,221
♪Perhaps someday,
we will look back on the past♪

689
00:29:54,222 --> 00:29:57,785
♪Ideals and vows.
How passionate they were♪

690
00:29:57,786 --> 00:30:03,889
♪Once, there was a moment so vivid♪

691
00:30:03,890 --> 00:30:04,920
Daji,

692
00:30:06,700 --> 00:30:09,170
I promise I'll give you
a life like this.

693
00:30:10,060 --> 00:30:11,280
I know.

694
00:30:12,260 --> 00:30:13,610
I'll work hard.

695
00:30:14,540 --> 00:30:16,130
Let's work hard together.

696
00:30:31,490 --> 00:30:33,649
(Spring 2024, Beijing)

697
00:30:33,650 --> 00:30:34,849
I'm Su Zihao.

698
00:30:34,850 --> 00:30:36,169
I'm Tong Leyi.

699
00:30:36,170 --> 00:30:38,169
Please bless me with a smooth graduation

700
00:30:38,170 --> 00:30:39,369
and early retirement.

701
00:30:39,370 --> 00:30:40,739
May my parents enjoy good health.

702
00:30:40,740 --> 00:30:43,299
Please grant me millions of followers,
loads of promotion projects,

703
00:30:43,300 --> 00:30:45,850
and a chance to work on
Paris and London Fashion Weeks.

704
00:31:14,450 --> 00:31:16,200
(God of Matchmaking Temple)
What are you doing?

705
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:19,170
This is the God of Matchmaking Temple.
It's for praying for love.

706
00:31:19,370 --> 00:31:20,299
Sorry to disturb.

707
00:31:20,300 --> 00:31:20,889
I'm so sorry.

708
00:31:20,890 --> 00:31:22,739
- Sorry.
- Hurry up and go.

709
00:31:22,740 --> 00:31:24,499
I accidentally prayed
to the God of Matchmaking.

710
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,499
Will I be okay?

711
00:31:25,500 --> 00:31:27,699
Don't tell me I'd suddenly
encounter guys later.

712
00:31:27,700 --> 00:31:28,979
Hard to say.

713
00:31:28,980 --> 00:31:30,849
Maybe you'll marry a guy
a few days later.

714
00:31:30,850 --> 00:31:31,739
Don't curse me.

715
00:31:31,740 --> 00:31:34,130
My career is taking off right now.

716
00:31:34,460 --> 00:31:36,200
I don't want any distractions.

717
00:31:37,930 --> 00:31:40,569
I read a post on a forum this morning.

718
00:31:40,570 --> 00:31:41,369
Someone asked

719
00:31:41,370 --> 00:31:43,610
why people stop dating anymore.

720
00:31:44,220 --> 00:31:46,259
It costs money.

721
00:31:46,260 --> 00:31:48,680
You have to pay for meals, shopping,

722
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:51,569
and gifts for Valentine's Day.

723
00:31:51,570 --> 00:31:56,129
Even if you're stingy, you still have to
get something for your girlfriend's birthday.

724
00:31:56,130 --> 00:31:57,409
Not only does it cost money,

725
00:31:57,410 --> 00:32:00,169
but it also takes time,
effort, and patience.

726
00:32:00,170 --> 00:32:01,929
Dating is like

727
00:32:01,930 --> 00:32:03,570
getting bled dry.

728
00:32:03,930 --> 00:32:06,330
Love is a luxury.

729
00:32:06,570 --> 00:32:09,499
Dating without money
is as unrealistic as buying Hermes

730
00:32:09,500 --> 00:32:11,650
when you only make 3,000 a month.

731
00:32:11,700 --> 00:32:14,720
Isn't that just like Scandalous Couple?

732
00:32:15,330 --> 00:32:16,170
Say,

733
00:32:16,330 --> 00:32:17,849
I set up the drive.

734
00:32:17,850 --> 00:32:19,480
Let's continue watching tonight.

735
00:32:19,850 --> 00:32:20,889
Not tonight.

736
00:32:20,890 --> 00:32:22,480
I'm flying to Hong Kong for work.

737
00:32:22,820 --> 00:32:25,050
Why are you so obsessed
with making money?

738
00:32:25,060 --> 00:32:26,960
Is your family poor?

739
00:32:28,650 --> 00:32:29,810
Yes.

740
00:32:30,020 --> 00:32:31,960
My parents died when I was little.

741
00:32:32,020 --> 00:32:34,440
I was left alone and helpless.

742
00:32:34,540 --> 00:32:35,850
Seriously?

743
00:32:38,500 --> 00:32:40,680
My ride's here. Bye.

744
00:32:46,130 --> 00:32:46,609
Zhou Shui,

745
00:32:46,610 --> 00:32:48,819
is the fan working or not?

746
00:32:48,820 --> 00:32:50,699
I can't feel the wind.

747
00:32:50,700 --> 00:32:52,520
I don't get it.

748
00:32:52,980 --> 00:32:56,330
If all the wind levels are the same,
why is it set into different levels?

749
00:32:59,500 --> 00:33:00,539
Oh no.

750
00:33:00,540 --> 00:33:02,440
I can't sleep like this.

751
00:33:03,130 --> 00:33:03,849
How about

752
00:33:03,850 --> 00:33:06,050
moving your legs close to the wall?

753
00:33:06,060 --> 00:33:09,329
I already stuck every part of my legs
against the wall.

754
00:33:09,330 --> 00:33:11,929
But the wall is hot too.

755
00:33:11,930 --> 00:33:13,650
It's useless.

756
00:33:14,090 --> 00:33:15,929
Gosh.

757
00:33:15,930 --> 00:33:17,739
I have to sell liquor tomorrow.

758
00:33:17,740 --> 00:33:20,280
The place is so far away.

759
00:33:20,930 --> 00:33:23,129
I need to take the bus, subway,

760
00:33:23,130 --> 00:33:25,000
and a rickshaw.

761
00:33:25,020 --> 00:33:27,409
And I need to set off before six.

762
00:33:27,410 --> 00:33:30,410
I can't fall asleep right now. Oh no!

763
00:33:31,570 --> 00:33:34,369
If only we had air conditioning.

764
00:33:34,370 --> 00:33:35,760
Let's buy one.

765
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:37,609
No way.

766
00:33:37,610 --> 00:33:38,779
- Why not?
- It's expensive.

767
00:33:38,780 --> 00:33:40,000
Don't buy it.

768
00:33:40,610 --> 00:33:42,920
How about a second-hand one?
We can afford that, right?

769
00:33:43,220 --> 00:33:44,810
It's also expensive.

770
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:47,059
Plus, the electricity bill.

771
00:33:47,060 --> 00:33:48,649
We need to save money.

772
00:33:48,650 --> 00:33:50,219
We haven't had enough money

773
00:33:50,220 --> 00:33:52,240
for next month's rent.

774
00:33:52,370 --> 00:33:56,650
And I don't want to throw this fan away.

775
00:33:58,570 --> 00:33:59,720
(Daji,)

776
00:34:00,370 --> 00:34:02,200
(are you broke?)

777
00:34:05,020 --> 00:34:07,200
We still have a little left.

778
00:34:07,650 --> 00:34:09,280
What's more important, movies or money?

779
00:34:10,100 --> 00:34:11,659
(But I can't buy you fried chicken)

780
00:34:11,660 --> 00:34:13,489
(when you're with me.)

781
00:34:13,490 --> 00:34:14,699
(That's not okay.)

782
00:34:14,700 --> 00:34:16,130
(I can provide for you.)

783
00:34:19,180 --> 00:34:21,050
Sorry, Daji.

784
00:34:21,820 --> 00:34:23,840
We had it tough.

785
00:34:23,970 --> 00:34:25,170
You're suffering.

786
00:34:26,970 --> 00:34:28,970
Stop talking.

787
00:34:29,370 --> 00:34:32,930
I need to fall asleep in five minutes.

788
00:34:35,930 --> 00:34:37,200
One last thing.

789
00:34:43,140 --> 00:34:46,760
I heard people in the photographic
equipment city are buying footage.

790
00:34:47,700 --> 00:34:48,930
I'll try selling some.

791
00:34:49,850 --> 00:34:50,760
What?

792
00:34:50,970 --> 00:34:51,970
Wait.

793
00:34:52,260 --> 00:34:54,849
We agreed to keep those.

794
00:34:54,850 --> 00:34:57,240
Someone between us has to make money.

795
00:34:57,700 --> 00:34:58,739
I'm saying

796
00:34:58,740 --> 00:35:00,489
I need to earn money.

797
00:35:00,490 --> 00:35:01,619
I can't leave that to you.

798
00:35:01,620 --> 00:35:03,960
What do you mean by
"someone between us has to make money"?

799
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:05,099
Am I not making money?

800
00:35:05,100 --> 00:35:06,329
I told you

801
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:08,650
to leave the money matter to me.

802
00:35:08,780 --> 00:35:10,969
Selling liquor is a lucrative job.

803
00:35:10,970 --> 00:35:13,090
We'll be fine once I get my commission.

804
00:35:13,140 --> 00:35:15,050
You don't have to worry about anything.

805
00:35:15,100 --> 00:35:16,369
Just focus on your movie.

806
00:35:16,370 --> 00:35:17,299
If you don't,

807
00:35:17,300 --> 00:35:18,849
that means you look down on me.

808
00:35:18,850 --> 00:35:20,130
Got it?

809
00:35:20,780 --> 00:35:22,489
Enough. Stop talking to me.

810
00:35:22,490 --> 00:35:24,200
I need to fall asleep

811
00:35:24,780 --> 00:35:27,570
in five minutes.

812
00:35:46,620 --> 00:35:47,659
Sorry.

813
00:35:47,660 --> 00:35:49,489
I told you to stop.

814
00:35:49,490 --> 00:35:50,099
Sorry.

815
00:35:50,100 --> 00:35:51,489
I thought you were asleep.

816
00:35:51,490 --> 00:35:53,720
How could I fall asleep that fast?

817
00:35:54,260 --> 00:35:55,329
I heard you snoring.

818
00:35:55,330 --> 00:35:57,680
Impossible. I don't snore.

819
00:36:01,330 --> 00:36:04,219
There are times when people hit rock bottom
and rise again to their prime.

820
00:36:04,220 --> 00:36:06,450
Don't look down on youth
who is in hard times.

821
00:36:06,970 --> 00:36:09,610
Smart youth makes the nation smart.

822
00:36:09,740 --> 00:36:12,299
Strong youth makes the nation strong.

823
00:36:12,300 --> 00:36:15,259
Lend them a light and they'll return
a bright future to the world.

824
00:36:15,260 --> 00:36:16,139
Mister,

825
00:36:16,140 --> 00:36:17,880
please buy my footage.

826
00:36:18,820 --> 00:36:19,970
No.

827
00:36:20,580 --> 00:36:20,969
I told you

828
00:36:20,970 --> 00:36:22,930
I really need money.

829
00:36:25,010 --> 00:36:25,889
Dude,

830
00:36:25,890 --> 00:36:27,049
do me this favor,

831
00:36:27,050 --> 00:36:28,179
and I'll put your name

832
00:36:28,180 --> 00:36:29,369
in all my movies in the future.

833
00:36:29,370 --> 00:36:31,299
Your name will leave a remarkable trace

834
00:36:31,300 --> 00:36:33,409
in Chinese film history.

835
00:36:33,410 --> 00:36:36,050
Your footage is too artsy.
No one will watch it.

836
00:36:36,140 --> 00:36:38,200
Mister, I'll do anything.

837
00:36:41,930 --> 00:36:43,240
What I mean

838
00:36:44,140 --> 00:36:46,139
is I can work for you.

839
00:36:46,140 --> 00:36:48,090
I'll do anything about film shooting.

840
00:36:48,620 --> 00:36:49,219
Oh, perfect.

841
00:36:49,220 --> 00:36:51,049
My friend needs someone
to shoot a documentary.

842
00:36:51,050 --> 00:36:52,360
Try that.

843
00:36:56,530 --> 00:36:58,489
You don't have to be so courteous.

844
00:36:58,490 --> 00:36:59,579
As a man,

845
00:36:59,580 --> 00:37:01,889
you need strong shoulders.

846
00:37:01,890 --> 00:37:03,050
I understood.

847
00:37:03,740 --> 00:37:05,299
Can you help me up first?

848
00:37:05,300 --> 00:37:05,849
Okay. Come.

849
00:37:05,850 --> 00:37:07,010
Thank you.

850
00:37:08,970 --> 00:37:09,929
Come.

851
00:37:09,930 --> 00:37:12,259
- All right. I need time to get used to it.
- Okay.

852
00:37:12,260 --> 00:37:13,320
Thank you, boss.

853
00:37:14,010 --> 00:37:17,170
What doesn't break you
will make you stronger.

854
00:37:23,530 --> 00:37:25,650
Are you a robot?

855
00:37:27,260 --> 00:37:28,049
Yes.

856
00:37:28,050 --> 00:37:30,720
Can you transform?

857
00:37:33,180 --> 00:37:34,659
I can't.

858
00:37:34,660 --> 00:37:35,819
I need the moon to transform.

859
00:37:35,820 --> 00:37:36,969
Liar.

860
00:37:36,970 --> 00:37:38,929
Transformers can transform.

861
00:37:38,930 --> 00:37:40,889
Only werewolves need the moon.

862
00:37:40,890 --> 00:37:42,699
Obviously, you don't watch movies.

863
00:37:42,700 --> 00:37:44,779
I'm not talking to you.
You're so insensible.

864
00:37:44,780 --> 00:37:45,739
He's disabled.

865
00:37:45,740 --> 00:37:47,929
We should help him.

866
00:37:47,930 --> 00:37:50,090
Sorry about that.

867
00:37:50,740 --> 00:37:52,579
Is your spine injured?

868
00:37:52,580 --> 00:37:55,259
You're lying. He's a robot.

869
00:37:55,260 --> 00:37:55,779
Look.

870
00:37:55,780 --> 00:37:57,139
This is a posture corrector.

871
00:37:57,140 --> 00:37:59,530
He can't stand without it.

872
00:37:59,740 --> 00:38:00,800
Am I right?

873
00:38:01,580 --> 00:38:02,099
Young man,

874
00:38:02,100 --> 00:38:02,779
sit here.

875
00:38:02,780 --> 00:38:03,450
Quick.

876
00:38:03,740 --> 00:38:04,179
Ma'am,

877
00:38:04,180 --> 00:38:04,779
no.

878
00:38:04,780 --> 00:38:05,969
I'm not sitting.

879
00:38:05,970 --> 00:38:06,409
Please sit.

880
00:38:06,410 --> 00:38:07,329
Please sit.

881
00:38:07,330 --> 00:38:08,090
You...

882
00:38:09,410 --> 00:38:11,200
I'm a young man.

883
00:38:11,330 --> 00:38:13,490
You're a young disabled man.

884
00:38:14,370 --> 00:38:15,720
Sit.

885
00:38:16,260 --> 00:38:17,699
Keep an eye on your boy.

886
00:38:17,700 --> 00:38:19,299
Boss, I've done my job.

887
00:38:19,300 --> 00:38:20,849
You should at least pay me for one day.

888
00:38:20,850 --> 00:38:21,819
You filmed rubbish.

889
00:38:21,820 --> 00:38:22,739
The crew said

890
00:38:22,740 --> 00:38:24,099
none of your footage is useful.

891
00:38:24,100 --> 00:38:24,739
Get lost now.

892
00:38:24,740 --> 00:38:25,889
- Go.
- Wait. What do you mean?

893
00:38:25,890 --> 00:38:28,280
- Why isn't my footage useful?
- Did you really do your job?

894
00:38:28,280 --> 00:38:30,099
I did exactly
what the crew wanted me to do.

895
00:38:30,100 --> 00:38:31,659
Did you pay me?

896
00:38:31,660 --> 00:38:32,760
Brat,

897
00:38:34,180 --> 00:38:35,449
why are you here?

898
00:38:35,450 --> 00:38:36,880
Why are you here?

899
00:38:37,140 --> 00:38:38,819
I'm asking for my pay.

900
00:38:38,820 --> 00:38:39,779
Did you get it?

901
00:38:39,780 --> 00:38:41,009
His work sucks.

902
00:38:41,010 --> 00:38:43,049
You just don't want to pay me.

903
00:38:43,050 --> 00:38:43,800
Bugger off.

904
00:38:44,490 --> 00:38:46,179
You guys move them to the truck.

905
00:38:46,180 --> 00:38:47,530
Wait for me.

906
00:38:51,620 --> 00:38:53,699
Is this all your equipment?

907
00:38:53,700 --> 00:38:54,739
It's for my job.

908
00:38:54,740 --> 00:38:55,880
Your job?

909
00:38:56,180 --> 00:38:57,329
You make movies too?

910
00:38:57,330 --> 00:38:59,179
I'm not that amazing.

911
00:38:59,180 --> 00:39:00,449
I shoot wedding mini-movies.

912
00:39:00,450 --> 00:39:02,090
I came up with this concept.

913
00:39:02,450 --> 00:39:04,680
Isn't that just wedding videos?

914
00:39:05,010 --> 00:39:07,130
It's fully customized.

915
00:39:07,180 --> 00:39:08,449
Starting at 30,000 yuan.

916
00:39:08,450 --> 00:39:09,889
30,000 for one wedding?

917
00:39:09,890 --> 00:39:11,400
Want to join me?

918
00:39:11,820 --> 00:39:13,329
You want me to do wedding videos?

919
00:39:13,330 --> 00:39:14,779
It's mini-movies!

920
00:39:14,780 --> 00:39:15,619
What mini-movies?

921
00:39:15,620 --> 00:39:17,409
Don't try to fool me
with the word "movie".

922
00:39:17,410 --> 00:39:18,259
I know what that is.

923
00:39:18,260 --> 00:39:19,009
It's not a movie.

924
00:39:19,010 --> 00:39:21,170
Not even close, okay?

925
00:39:22,530 --> 00:39:23,650
Fine.

926
00:39:32,100 --> 00:39:35,739
Brat, swallow your pride
and join me for a couple of gigs.

927
00:39:35,740 --> 00:39:38,130
The money's easy. Not interested?

928
00:39:38,260 --> 00:39:39,819
I need to focus on my own movies.

929
00:39:39,820 --> 00:39:41,099
Just two gigs.

930
00:39:41,100 --> 00:39:43,009
- We can continue with...
- Stay out of my business.

931
00:39:43,010 --> 00:39:45,130
I'll figure out my own way.

932
00:39:45,180 --> 00:39:47,970
An angry idiot.

933
00:39:48,220 --> 00:39:49,580
Call me when you change your mind.

934
00:39:51,300 --> 00:39:52,360
You can make lots of money.

935
00:39:57,620 --> 00:39:59,139
Pay me 100 yuan, okay?

936
00:39:59,140 --> 00:40:00,050
Get lost.

937
00:40:23,300 --> 00:40:24,099
Hello, boss?

938
00:40:24,100 --> 00:40:25,259
You again?

939
00:40:25,260 --> 00:40:26,619
Why are you calling again?

940
00:40:26,620 --> 00:40:28,889
Can I try out for the crew
again tomorrow?

941
00:40:28,890 --> 00:40:29,929
Can you give me a refund?

942
00:40:29,930 --> 00:40:31,049
This liquor is fake.

943
00:40:31,050 --> 00:40:32,699
No, mister. We...

944
00:40:32,700 --> 00:40:34,819
You can't get a refund
after drinking it.

945
00:40:34,820 --> 00:40:35,739
I drank a bottle

946
00:40:35,740 --> 00:40:37,720
and slept till morning.

947
00:40:37,740 --> 00:40:40,619
That's because you drank
the whole bottle in one go.

948
00:40:40,620 --> 00:40:41,819
You're supposed to sip it.

949
00:40:41,820 --> 00:40:42,409
Yes.

950
00:40:42,410 --> 00:40:44,259
How about you buy another box
and try again?

951
00:40:44,260 --> 00:40:45,409
See how well it works.

952
00:40:45,410 --> 00:40:46,619
I can call the police

953
00:40:46,620 --> 00:40:48,889
and have you arrested for soliciting.

954
00:40:48,890 --> 00:40:50,369
We're not escorts.

955
00:40:50,370 --> 00:40:52,200
We're selling liquor.

956
00:40:52,260 --> 00:40:53,819
Look what you're wearing.

957
00:40:53,820 --> 00:40:55,530
It's too revealing.

958
00:40:55,820 --> 00:40:57,480
You even lied about
staying up till 3 AM.

959
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:59,659
I know you're selling fake booze
by the day,

960
00:40:59,660 --> 00:41:01,009
- and sell yourself by night.
- Watch your mouth.

961
00:41:01,010 --> 00:41:02,779
How could you talk like that?

962
00:41:02,780 --> 00:41:04,299
You're insulting us.

963
00:41:04,300 --> 00:41:05,969
We're not escorts.

964
00:41:05,970 --> 00:41:07,049
Calm down, mister.

965
00:41:07,050 --> 00:41:08,400
How could you bully women?

966
00:41:08,580 --> 00:41:11,489
- What's going on here?
- How could you talk like that?

967
00:41:11,490 --> 00:41:14,329
- If this isn't an insult, then what is?
- Jingshu, what's going on here?

968
00:41:14,330 --> 00:41:16,360
- You bully women.
- What do you think you're doing?

969
00:41:16,360 --> 00:41:17,654
Listen, don't hurt him.

970
00:41:17,655 --> 00:41:18,179
Don't fight.

971
00:41:18,180 --> 00:41:19,320
Let's talk it out.

972
00:41:19,330 --> 00:41:20,489
Back off.

973
00:41:20,490 --> 00:41:21,880
So what I pushed you?

974
00:41:22,140 --> 00:41:23,619
- Calm down.
- Don't point fingers.

975
00:41:23,620 --> 00:41:25,219
- Don't fight.
- Hit him if you dare.

976
00:41:25,220 --> 00:41:27,600
- Don't fight, did you hear me?
- Jingshu, put your coat on.

977
00:41:27,600 --> 00:41:29,680
- Don't touch him.
- Let's speak nicely.

978
00:41:30,180 --> 00:41:32,050
- Don't fight.
- Jingshu, don't rush in.

979
00:41:32,410 --> 00:41:33,219
Don't rush in.

980
00:41:33,220 --> 00:41:33,929
Don't fight.

981
00:41:33,930 --> 00:41:35,489
This is dangerous. Quit the job.

982
00:41:35,490 --> 00:41:37,409
- But it pays well.
- I'll earn money.

983
00:41:37,410 --> 00:41:39,840
- This is really lucrative.
- We made 800 in a day.

984
00:41:40,140 --> 00:41:42,369
I can support you in making movies.

985
00:41:42,370 --> 00:41:44,139
Don't do this kind of job anymore.

986
00:41:44,140 --> 00:41:45,299
Focus on school.

987
00:41:45,300 --> 00:41:47,010
I'll pay for your rent.

988
00:41:47,780 --> 00:41:49,659
What? Who?

989
00:41:49,660 --> 00:41:51,840
I said I'd pay Jingshu's rent.

990
00:42:11,330 --> 00:42:12,450
Hello?

991
00:42:13,100 --> 00:42:14,200
Who's speaking?

992
00:42:16,740 --> 00:42:18,170
For real?

993
00:42:19,850 --> 00:42:20,880
Thank you.

994
00:42:21,530 --> 00:42:22,680
Zhou Shui,

995
00:42:23,140 --> 00:42:24,849
I got a job.

996
00:42:24,850 --> 00:42:26,299
Speak nicely.

997
00:42:26,300 --> 00:42:27,320
Let's talk this through.

998
00:42:28,660 --> 00:42:31,840
I got a job!

999
00:42:34,820 --> 00:42:36,880
A real job.

1000
00:42:41,530 --> 00:42:43,450
(Life is full of wonders.)

1001
00:42:43,890 --> 00:42:46,090
(It gives you the "Beautiful" job offer)

1002
00:42:46,100 --> 00:42:48,680
(when you're at your lowest.)

1003
00:42:48,740 --> 00:42:50,680
What does that have to do with us?

1004
00:42:54,100 --> 00:42:55,010
What?

1005
00:42:56,850 --> 00:42:59,240
(But it also takes something away)

1006
00:42:59,970 --> 00:43:01,760
(during your happiest moments.)

1007
00:43:21,200 --> 00:43:24,710
♪Please, put away your compromises♪

1008
00:43:25,080 --> 00:43:29,059
♪Get closer to the ideal world♪

1009
00:43:29,060 --> 00:43:34,660
♪Even if that day
comes a little slower and lonelier♪

1010
00:43:36,120 --> 00:43:39,780
♪A person's broken copper and iron♪

1011
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:43,740
♪Still has to be forged
into their own sword♪

1012
00:43:43,810 --> 00:43:48,079
♪Dare to scorn, dare to be passionate,
dare to write♪

1013
00:43:48,080 --> 00:43:52,390
♪The plot of a hero's story♪

1014
00:43:53,240 --> 00:43:57,539
♪The brave person says goodbye first♪

1015
00:43:57,540 --> 00:44:01,269
♪The love that's worth it
is always sorry♪

1016
00:44:01,270 --> 00:44:05,199
♪Once we were bold and fearless,
fighting against the world♪

1017
00:44:05,200 --> 00:44:08,579
♪Only later realizing
how small and pitiful we were♪

1018
00:44:08,580 --> 00:44:12,759
♪The brave person says goodbye♪

1019
00:44:12,760 --> 00:44:16,669
♪The love that's worth it
still leaves us in debt♪

1020
00:44:16,670 --> 00:44:19,999
♪If we were more cautious
and didn't take risks back then♪

1021
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:23,619
♪We might have our own fatigue♪

1022
00:44:23,620 --> 00:44:26,180
♪Don't long for it♪

1023
00:44:27,710 --> 00:44:31,290
♪Please answer me, I want to understand♪

1024
00:44:31,880 --> 00:44:35,699
♪Love is worth the passion,
worth the dark night♪

1025
00:44:35,700 --> 00:44:42,250
♪Worth the stubbornness
to light up moments of flickering light♪

1026
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:46,300
♪Even if we know the story's ending♪

1027
00:44:46,610 --> 00:44:50,459
♪We still dare to pull on each other
a few more times♪

1028
00:44:50,460 --> 00:44:54,759
♪There is a trial
worth being stubborn, worth writing♪

1029
00:44:54,760 --> 00:44:59,470
♪That's the chapter we loved♪

1030
00:45:01,750 --> 00:45:05,999
♪The brave person says goodbye first♪

1031
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:09,839
♪The love that's worth it
is always sorry♪

1032
00:45:09,840 --> 00:45:13,709
♪Once we were bold and fearless,
fighting against the world♪

1033
00:45:13,710 --> 00:45:17,159
♪Only later realizing
how small and pitiful we were♪

1034
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:21,339
♪If the ending could truly be seen♪

1035
00:45:21,340 --> 00:45:25,109
♪Would we still dare to meet?♪

1036
00:45:25,110 --> 00:45:28,639
♪As long as you say a time and place♪

1037
00:45:28,640 --> 00:45:31,779
♪I will still show up,
no regrets, no complaints♪

1038
00:45:31,780 --> 00:45:34,630
♪I would rather♪
